### **Q10: Write a JavaScript program that displays four buttons named "Red," "Blue," "Green," and "Yellow." On clicking any of these buttons, the code displays the message that you have selected that particular color.**

```javascript
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Color Selector</title>
</head>
<body>
  <button onclick="selectColor('Red')">Red</button>
  <button onclick="selectColor('Blue')">Blue</button>
  <button onclick="selectColor('Green')">Green</button>
  <button onclick="selectColor('Yellow')">Yellow</button>

  <p id="message"></p>

  <script>
    function selectColor(color) {
      document.getElementById('message').textContent = `You selected ${color}`;
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
```

